aa(lp55
VSo we talk about PMTCT,
p56
aVand we refer to PMTCT, prevention of mother to child transmission.
p57
aVI think there's an assumption amongst most people in the public
p58
aVthat if a mother is HIV-positive,
p59
aVshe's going to infect her child.
p60
aVThe reality is really, very different.
p61
aVIn resource-rich countries,
p62
aVwith all the tests and treatment we currently have,
p63
aVless than two percent of babies are born HIV-positive \u2014
p64
aV98 percent of babies are born HIV-negative.
p65
aVAnd yet, the reality in resource-poor countries,
p66
aVin the absence of tests and treatment,
p67
aV40 percent \u2014 40 percent of children are infected \u2014
p68
aV40 percent versus two percent \u2014
p69
aVan enormous difference.
p70
aVSo these programs \u2014
p71
aVand I'm going to refer to PMTCT though my talk \u2014
p72
aVthese prevention programs,
p73
aVsimply, they're the tests and the drugs that we give to mothers
p74
aVto prevent them from infecting their babies,
p75
aVand also the medicines we give to mothers
p76
aVto keep them healthy and alive to raise their children.
p77
aVSo it's the test a mother gets when she comes in.
p78
aVIt's the drugs she receives
p79
aVto protect the baby that's inside the uterus and during delivery.
p80
aVIt's the guidance she gets around infant feeding
p81
aVand safer sex.
p82
aVIt's an entire package of services,
p83
aVand it works.
p84
aa(lp85
VSo in the United States,
p86
aVsince the advent of treatment in the middle of the 1990s,
p87
aVthere's been an 80-percent decline
p88
aVin the number of HIV-infected children.
p89
aVLess than 100 babies are born with HIV
p90
aVeach year in the United States
p91
aVand yet, still,
p92
aVover 400,000 children
p93
aVare born every year in the world today with HIV.
p94
aVWhat does that mean?
p95
aVIt means 1,100 children infected each day \u2014
p96
aV1,100 children each day, infected with HIV.
p97
aVAnd where do they come from?
p98
aVWell, less than one comes from the United States.
p99
aVOne, on average, comes from Europe.
p100
aV100 come from Asia and the Pacific.
p101
aVAnd each day,
p102
aVa thousand babies \u2014 a thousand babies
p103
aVare born each day with HIV in Africa.
