aa(lp144
VThis is a picture of a maternal health clinic in Africa \u2014
p145
aVmothers coming, pregnant and with their babies.
p146
aVThese women are here for care,
p147
aVbut we know that just doing a test,
p148
aVjust giving someone a drug,
p149
aVit's not enough.
p150
aVMeds don't equal medical care.
p151
aVDoctors and nurses, frankly,
p152
aVdon't have the time or skills
p153
aVto tell people what to do in ways they understand.
p154
aVI'm a doctor \u2014 I tell people things to do,
p155
aVand I expect them to follow my guidance \u2014
p156
aVbecause I'm a doctor; I went to Harvard \u2014
p157
aVbut the reality is,
p158
aVif I tell a patient, "You should have safer sex.
p159
aVYou should always use a condom,"
p160
aVand yet, in her relationship, she's not empowered \u2014
p161
aVwhat's going to happen?
p162
aVIf I tell her to take her medicines every day
p163
aVand yet, no one in the household knows about her illness, so
p164
aVit's just not going to work.
